Amnon: Ambrosian, 71:11 cent. METER: Iambie dimeter. TRANSLATION by Robert Campbell. There are about thirty translations. First line of Original Text: Ad coenam Aym' providi. LITURGICAL Usa: Vespers hymn from Low Sunday to Ascension Day. This hymn was greatly altered by the re- visers under Urban VIII (1632) ; only three lines remained unaltered. There are ten translations of this hymn in Mr. Shipley's Annus Sanctus, both texts being represented. Of the translations of the Roman Breviary Text, Mr. Camp- bell's is more extensively used than all others combined. It is not so literal as some other translations, but it is a hymn of great beauty, and it is not surprising that it is found in so many hymn books.
